# Multi-Account Example Configuration

# ================================================================
# MULTI-ACCOUNT MODE
# ================================================================
# Use this format to run multiple accounts concurrently
#
# Each account needs:
#   EMAIL_X       - TaskFlux account email (required)
#   PASSWORD_X    - TaskFlux account password (required) 
#   NTFY_URL_X    - Notification URL (optional, falls back to NTFY_URL)
#
# Replace X with account number (1, 2, 3, etc.)
# ================================================================

# Account 1
EMAIL_1=account1@gmail.com
PASSWORD_1=your_password_here
NTFY_URL_1=https://ntfy.sh/taskflux_account1

# Account 2
EMAIL_2=account2@gmail.com
PASSWORD_2=your_password_here
NTFY_URL_2=https://ntfy.sh/taskflux_account2

# Account 3
EMAIL_3=account3@gmail.com
PASSWORD_3=your_password_here
NTFY_URL_3=https://ntfy.sh/taskflux_account3

# Shared/Fallback notification URL (optional)
# Used when NTFY_URL_X is not specified for an account
NTFY_URL=https://ntfy.sh/taskflux_all


# ================================================================
# SINGLE ACCOUNT MODE (BACKWARD COMPATIBILITY)
# ================================================================
# If EMAIL_1 is not found, the bot runs in single account mode
# using these variables:
# ================================================================

# EMAIL=your_email@gmail.com
# PASSWORD=your_password
# NTFY_URL=https://ntfy.sh/your_topic


# ================================================================
# NOTES
# ================================================================
# - Each account runs independently in its own thread
# - Cooldowns are tracked separately per account in cooldown_accountX.json
# - Notifications include account prefix: [Acc 1], [Acc 2], etc.
# - You can use different ntfy topics for each account
# - To run just 2 accounts, only configure EMAIL_1 and EMAIL_2
# ================================================================
